      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The Supreme Court's modern interpretation often departs significantly from what many believe the Founders intended with the 2nd Amendment. Originalists argue it was meant strictly for militia formation, not individual gun ownership. In contrast, living constitutionalists believe the right to bear arms encompasses modern forms of defense. To me, originalist interpretations seem more legally sound because they closely adhere to historical context and framers' intent. Ultimately, the Supreme Court's rulings reflect evolving societal values and judicial philosophies, which may or may not align with Founding Era interpretations.",
