      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I think the \"living constitution\" approach isn't just pushing politics but addressing real-world issues. Law can't stay stagnant if society changes; it's there to reflect current needs. I'm in favor of a dynamic interpretation that sees the 2nd Amendment as protecting modern forms of defense, not just archaic militias. That way, it's relevant to today's challenges and protects individuals from oppressive governments, which I view as a cornerstone principle. I believe adapting the law to fit contemporary scenarios keeps its spirit alive.",
